The paper deals with privacy attacks on aggregate location data, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also extensively uses machine learning techniques to perform the attacks, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with data management and privacy-preserving mechanisms, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the impact of different parameters on the effectiveness of the attacks, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the attacks for privacy regulation, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of computers and society (cs.CY).
